designer sonia rykiel says her latest collection is a celebration of women . elsa klensch takes us on the runway for a sophisticated glimpse of her work . reporter : always an intellectual , designer sonia rykiel celebrates 30 years in fashion with a show at the new , modern library in paris . and rykiel does n't disappoint . she does exaggerated cardigans , long skirts , full pants , curvaceous sweaters , colorful striped tops , and easy jackets . the place like that , the place needs something fantastic , something magic . the girls have to be magic , the clothes have to be magic , the music has to be magic . you ca n't use a place like that if you are not about to have a space like that . reporter : what gave you the idea to show in the library ? why not ? i love words . i love books . reporter : tell me , how has the 30 years of fashion designing influenced this collection ? you know , i think my work is but it 's an evolution , it 's not a revolution . but it 's true that now my purpose in fashion is to express what a woman of today , a woman of tomorrow can go , and can do in the world , in a political way , in a social way . reporter : have you got very many patterns in the daytime ? i have a lot of plaids . i have a lot of scottish tartans . i love , i love . and also , flanle with stripes . and also a lot of flowers in those fabric . reporter : what 's evening like ? very sophisticated . very , very sophisticated with a lot of lace , of muslin and printed muslin , very nice . reporter : long dresses ? long dresses , and also jackets in velvet , printed with big pants in velvet also for evening . reporter : that 's sonia rykiel with her fall\/winter collection . elsa klensch , cnn , paris . 